posts_info.description: 😒They didn’t have to do me like that! 😭 A little backstory: When I was younger, I wanted to be a singer. Watching Beyoncé and Rihanna, I just knew that was what I was meant to do! I was always in the choir and even forced my parents to pay for private voice lessons. I would practice every day for years. One day, I just accepted the fact that singing was not a talent God gave me. We all know that people with raspy voices are the best singers, so when I got sick and started losing my voice, I thought maybe now I would be able to sing. So, I sat my family down like I used to when I was younger and asked them to listen to me sing. Except now I’m a lot older, so they have no problem hurting my feelings. Whereas before, they would listen to me and tell me I’m getting better, now they laugh hysterically! 😫😭

Cast all of your burdens on Jesus Christ and know that it is just a season. You will come out the other side stronger and more alive and tou will look back at this season and have a story to tell!  Love you! ❤️

Leaving was the best thing I ever did… I worked in corporate America for 11 years before taking leave to take care of my children. The child care system failed me and my family and I couldn’t stand barely seeing my children anymore. Something had to change.  How did I do it? Before I left work I started selling my old items on Poshmark to make extra money. I quickly realized I could make money off of items I found at thrift stores, estate sales, and yard sales. I could feel this would be something that was going to be what helped me and my family through this tough time. Now you can make Mozzarella Cheese at home 🧀  Recipe ⬇️ RECETA ⬇️ Very easy 2 ingredient mozzarella cheese so you can make at home. So simple and delicious! ☺️🧀 Está receta solo ocupa 2 ingredientes🫶🏼  Recipe: • 5 liters of raw cow’s milk or low-temp pasteurized whole milk. You can NOT use ultra pasteurized milk.  • 200 ml of vinegar (I used white) • Heat milk to 46° C , take off heat, add vinegar, stir to combine for about 25 seconds, cover with lid and leave for 10 minutes.  • remove cheese curds from the liquid whey and shape into balls. Squeeze out as much whey as possible.  • heat whey back up to 65° C and add the balls of mozzarella back in for 30 second increments each. Take out and stretch until it becomes stretchy and smooth. Do this about 3-5 times until nice and smooth.  • Shape into balls and add salt if you’d like  • place balls into room temp or iced whey/water in the fridge for up to 1 week Enjoy☺️  RECETA: • 5 litros de leche de vaca cruda o leche entera pasteurizada a baja temperatura  • 200 ml de vinagre blanco • Calienta la leche hasta que alcance una temperatura de 46° C, remueve del fuego, agrega el vinagre, mezcla por unos 25 segundos. cubrir con tapa y déjalo por 10 minutos.  • retire la cuajada de queso del suero de leche. Darle forma de bolas. exprime la mayor cantidad de líquido posible  • calienta el suero de leche a 65° C y agrega las bolas de mozzarella por 30 segundos cada uno. Saca y estira hasta que quede elástico y suave. Repite este proceso 3-5 veces. Hasta que todas las bolas estén bien suaves.  • formar bolas con el queso y añade sal  • guardar el queso mozzarella a temperatura ambiente o en agua helada/ suero helada en la nevera hasta por una semana  #mozzarella #mozzarellacheese #homemadecheese #gabrielavlogs #gabrielamkv #cheeserecipes #EasyRecipes #Recipe #recetas #queso #quesomozzarella #quesocasero

posts_info.description: If you’ve got water, oil, and food coloring you can do this fun “fireworks” in a jar experiment today! 🎆 Save this post and read the instructions and tips below! Happy New Years, my friends! ❤️ WHAT YOU’LL NEED: Clear glass or jar Water Cooking oil (vegetable or baby oil) Liquid food coloring (various colors) Small dish Fork or stirrer HOW TO 1️⃣ Fill the glass about three-quarters full with water. 2️⃣ In a small dish, mix a few drops of liquid food coloring with a small amount of cooking oil. Stir gently to combine. 3️⃣ Pour the colored oil mixture into the glass of water. 4️⃣ Observe as the colored oil mixture disperses through the water, creating vibrant bursts of color. Pro Tip: don’t overmix the food coloring or pour the oil mixture into the glass too fast or else you may end up with a black glass of water!! THE SCIENCE  The Fireworks in a Jar experiment demonstrates the principle of immiscibility and varying densities of liquids, as the colored oil, being less dense than water, creates bursts of color like fireworks when introduced into the water-filled jar. #kidactivities #stemeducation #playideas #scienceexperimentsforkids #scienceforkids
